Class SortableCollection<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • craterdog.smart.SmartObject<Collection<E>>
      • craterdog.collections.abstractions.Collection<E>
        • craterdog.collections.abstractions.OpenCollection<E>
          • craterdog.collections.abstractions.SortableCollection<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element managed by the collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Accessible<E>, Dynamic<E>, Sortable<E>, Composite, Sequential<E>, java.lang.Comparable<Collection<E>>, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    List, Map

    public abstract class SortableCollection<E>
extends OpenCollection<E>
implements Sortable<E>
    This abstract class defines the invariant methods that all sortable collections must inherit. A sortable collection allows the order of its elements to be determined externally. By default, the elements will be placed in the order in which they were added to the collection. Additionally, the elements can be sorted in various ways depending on a specified sorting algorithm and comparison function.
    Author:
    Derk Norton
